<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="86" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1580,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,1580,1604]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Description.</emphasis>
Yellowish-brown species. Color pattern of anterior dorsum and face as in 
<figureCitation box="[1096,1192,1580,1603]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="1.[151,257,1377,1398]" captionTargetBox="[151,1415,313,1347]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,313,1368]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Connectivus bifidus sp. nov.: 1, 3, dorsal view; 2, 3, Face; 3, 3, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282507/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">
Figs 
<number box="[1150,1192,1580,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
</figureCitation>
. Vertex with four dark brown marks on anterior margin. Legs marked with brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1580,2020]" box="[199,717,1650,1673]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Other external features as in generic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1580,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis box="[199,364,1684,1707]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Male pygofer without processes, the male anal tube partially sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1257,1684,1707]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 17" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1904,1925]" captionTargetBox="[174,1406,226,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,218,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 17. Connectivus bifidus sp. nov.: 4, Veins of forewing; 5, Hindwing; 6, Fore femur and tibia, anterior surface; 7, Apex of hind femur, anterior surface; 8, Hind tibia, dorsal surface; 9, Hind tibia, ventral surface; 10, Hind tarsus, ventral surface; 11, Male pygofer side, lateral view; 12, Valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 13, Aedeagus, ventral view; 14, Aedeagus, lateral view; 15, Connective, ventral view; 16, Connective, lateral view; 17, Style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282508/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">
Fig. 
<number box="[1229,1257,1684,1707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Valve fused to subgenital plates, approximately triangular, apically pointed, conjioned to just over half length, with a row of macrosetae along lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[380,461,1754,1777]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 17" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1904,1925]" captionTargetBox="[174,1406,226,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,218,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 17. Connectivus bifidus sp. nov.: 4, Veins of forewing; 5, Hindwing; 6, Fore femur and tibia, anterior surface; 7, Apex of hind femur, anterior surface; 8, Hind tibia, dorsal surface; 9, Hind tibia, ventral surface; 10, Hind tarsus, ventral surface; 11, Male pygofer side, lateral view; 12, Valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 13, Aedeagus, ventral view; 14, Aedeagus, lateral view; 15, Connective, ventral view; 16, Connective, lateral view; 17, Style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282508/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">
Fig. 
<number box="[431,461,1754,1777]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft longer than three times length of connective (
<figureCitation box="[1132,1257,1754,1777]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 17" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1904,1925]" captionTargetBox="[174,1406,226,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,218,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 17. Connectivus bifidus sp. nov.: 4, Veins of forewing; 5, Hindwing; 6, Fore femur and tibia, anterior surface; 7, Apex of hind femur, anterior surface; 8, Hind tibia, dorsal surface; 9, Hind tibia, ventral surface; 10, Hind tarsus, ventral surface; 11, Male pygofer side, lateral view; 12, Valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 13, Aedeagus, ventral view; 14, Aedeagus, lateral view; 15, Connective, ventral view; 16, Connective, lateral view; 17, Style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282508/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
). Connective, its stem nearly 
<number box="[281,290,1788,1811]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[300,315,1788,1811]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" value="2.0">2</number>
length of arms (
<figureCitation box="[491,620,1788,1811]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 17" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1904,1925]" captionTargetBox="[174,1406,226,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,218,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 17. Connectivus bifidus sp. nov.: 4, Veins of forewing; 5, Hindwing; 6, Fore femur and tibia, anterior surface; 7, Apex of hind femur, anterior surface; 8, Hind tibia, dorsal surface; 9, Hind tibia, ventral surface; 10, Hind tarsus, ventral surface; 11, Male pygofer side, lateral view; 12, Valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 13, Aedeagus, ventral view; 14, Aedeagus, lateral view; 15, Connective, ventral view; 16, Connective, lateral view; 17, Style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282508/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Figs. 15, 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1580,2020]" box="[199,841,1823,1847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,373,1823,1847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Measurements.</emphasis>
